Read in RDB table

Source: R/rdb.gen.R
read_tbl.Rd

Fetches a table from the RDB DBMS's public schema and returns it as a tibble.

Usage

read_tbl(
  tbl_name = tbl_metadata$name,
  connection = connect(),
  disconnect = TRUE
)

Arguments

tbl_name

Table name. One of "actors", "options", "legal_norms", "referendum_types", "referendums", "referendum_titles", "referendum_questions", "referendum_positions", "referendum_votes", "referendum_sub_votes", "countries", "subnational_entities", "municipalities" and "languages".

connection

Database connection to RDB's PostgreSQL DBMS. An S4 object that inherits from DBI::DBIConnection.

disconnect

Whether or not to terminate the database connection when finished.

Value

A tibble.

See also

Other data functions: assert_vars(), delete_rfrnds(), download_file_attachment(), rfrnd_types(), rfrnds(), rfrnds_old(), validate_rfrnds()
